      <section eId="sec_CHC-572">
        <num>CHC 572</num>
        <heading>572.  Definitions</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-572__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>&quot;Child abuse and neglect case&quot; means a child protection proceeding conducted
by a court exercising juvenile jurisdiction involving the abuse or neglect of children as
provided specifically in Titles VI, X, and XI of this Code.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-572__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>&quot;Indigent Parents' Program&quot; means the Indigent Parents' Representation Program
established in accordance with Article 574.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=451562</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
